Abstract—Swarm intelligence is an effective tool to deal with complex systems. Based on distinctive models, a stochastic model of a swarm system is proposed in this paper, in which agents in the swarm moved to its center. Moreover, stability of the system is discussed by Lyapunov function, and the conditions of swarm convergence are presented.
